00:14:21.358 --> 00:14:24.153
I don't know. Like. five people.

263
00:14:24.236 --> 00:14:27.448
I don't understand how it is that
I'm always getting screwed with.

264
00:14:27.531 --> 00:14:29.158
but I'm the one that gets
sent to the office?

265
00:14:29.241 --> 00:14:30.743
Well. let's start with...

266
00:14:32.203 --> 00:14:34.205
what is it that you can do
to protect yourself?

267
00:14:34.914 --> 00:14:38.042
What is anything you're doing
that might provoke kids?

268
00:14:38.626 --> 00:14:39.543
Are you serious?

269
00:14:41.545 --> 00:14:43.756
That's convenient. Blame the victim.

270
00:14:43.839 --> 00:14:45.091
No. no one's blaming anyone.

271
00:14:45.174 --> 00:14:46.801
Okay. well. maybe we should be.

272
00:14:48.469 --> 00:14:52.932
You should be blaming the kids
that make this school a terrible place.

273
00:14:54.058 --> 00:14:57.103
You should be blaming the kids that
make other kids want to kill themselves.

274
00:14:59.271 --> 00:15:00.731
Are you referring to Hannah Baker?

275
00:15:00.815 --> 00:15:02.066
What do you think?

276
00:15:04.443 --> 00:15:05.820
Do you want to talk about Hannah?

277
00:15:06.529 --> 00:15:07.571
Do you?

278
00:15:09.156 --> 00:15:10.491
If it's on your mind.

279
00:15:11.283 --> 00:15:12.493
Isn't it on yours?

280
00:15:15.538 --> 00:15:16.705
Of course.

281
00:15:19.291 --> 00:15:20.626
Yeah. I bet it is.

282
00:15:21.710 --> 00:15:23.254
- Tyler.
- Nah. thanks.

283
00:15:23.337 --> 00:15:24.505
Tyler.

284
00:15:35.808 --> 00:15:37.476
I don't know what Justin's going to do.

285
00:15:37.560 --> 00:15:39.979
He says he wants to shut Clay down.

286
00:15:40.062 --> 00:15:41.564
We tried that.

287
00:15:41.647 --> 00:15:43.440
Clay must have listened to his tape.

288
00:15:43.524 --> 00:15:46.026
I told you. he listens to his tape.
everything changes.

289
00:15:46.110 --> 00:15:48.154
He hasn't listen to his tape.
He just heard Tyler.

290
00:15:48.237 --> 00:15:50.072
He didn't say anything
about Jessica's party.

291
00:15:50.156 --> 00:15:52.992
But when he does.
he'll probably believe Hannah.

292
00:15:53.367 --> 00:15:54.785
He won't know that she's lying.

293
00:15:58.164 --> 00:15:59.623
Clay's mom came to see Bolan.

294
00:16:00.833 --> 00:16:02.209
What? Why?

295
00:16:02.543 --> 00:16:03.878
What else could it be?

296
00:16:03.961 --> 00:16:05.629
Clay wouldn't tell his mom
about the tapes.

297
00:16:05.713 --> 00:16:07.923
Why not? He wasn't shy about Tyler.

298
00:16:08.007 --> 00:16:09.925
That would be so messed up
if he told his mom.

299
00:16:10.467 --> 00:16:12.428
I'm with Justin.
We need to do something serious.

300
00:16:12.678 --> 00:16:14.346
What. so your mom doesn't find out?

301
00:16:14.430 --> 00:16:16.307
Yeah. among other people.
like maybe your dad.

302
00:16:16.390 --> 00:16:18.851
What can we do.
if he's already ratted us out?

303
00:16:19.185 --> 00:16:22.021
I'm on track for valedictorian.
I do not need this shit.

304
00:16:22.104 --> 00:16:25.858
Yes. Marcus. the most important thing
right now is your valedictorian speech.

305
00:16:25.941 --> 00:16:27.151
Let's keep that in mind.

306
00:16:27.234 --> 00:16:28.360
You talking about Clay?

307
00:16:28.694 --> 00:16:30.112
Keep your voice down. dude.

308
00:16:31.405 --> 00:16:32.990
Whatever you're doing. I want in.

309
00:16:33.073 --> 00:16:35.326
We're not doing anything. Tyler.

310
00:16:36.702 --> 00:16:38.787
It's not like we would trust you
if we were.

311
00:16:41.707 --> 00:16:43.125
This... this isn't fair.

312
00:16:43.209 --> 00:16:44.877
Dude. get the hell out.

313
00:16:45.419 --> 00:16:46.337
Seriously.

314
00:16:46.670 --> 00:16:48.631
I have a right to be here. guys...

315
00:16:48.714 --> 00:16:50.841
I will snap your arm in two.

316
00:16:58.557 --> 00:16:59.767
Let me deal with it.

317
00:17:00.351 --> 00:17:01.727
Okay? Quietly.

318
00:17:02.811 --> 00:17:04.188
No snapping of arms.

319
00:17:10.402 --> 00:17:12.529
<i>For days after Tyler's
picture went around.</i>

320
00:17:12.613 --> 00:17:14.031
<i>I tried to catch your eye.</i>

321
00:17:19.203 --> 00:17:20.955
<i>You ignored me for weeks.</i>

322
00:17:22.122 --> 00:17:24.166
<i>But I decided enough was enough.</i>

323
00:17:25.417 --> 00:17:26.752
<i>I wanted to talk to you.</i>

324
00:17:27.836 --> 00:17:30.089
<i>I mean. we were in this together...</i>

325
00:17:30.881 --> 00:17:31.715
<i>weren't we?</i>

326
00:17:33.300 --> 00:17:34.426
Hey.

327
00:17:34.510 --> 00:17:35.803
That seat's taken.

328
00:17:36.053 --> 00:17:37.388
Yeah. by me.

329
00:17:39.515 --> 00:17:40.432
Talk to me.

330
00:17:40.516 --> 00:17:41.350
About what?

331
00:17:42.184 --> 00:17:43.227
I thought we were friends.

332
00:17:43.560 --> 00:17:44.853
We are friends.

333
00:17:46.313 --> 00:17:47.606
I mean. it seemed like we were.

334
00:17:48.315 --> 00:17:50.943
Whatever you're going through now.
you don't have to do it alone.

335
00:17:51.026 --> 00:17:52.319
I don't know what you're talking about.

336
00:17:52.403 --> 00:17:53.696
Like you said...

337
00:17:54.571 --> 00:17:56.740
I know what it feels like
to have people judge you.

338
00:17:57.866 --> 00:17:58.909
And it sucks.

339
00:17:59.451 --> 00:18:02.371
And it helps to have a friend
who doesn't judge you.

340
00:18:03.789 --> 00:18:05.624
I thought we were eating together.

341
00:18:09.295 --> 00:18:11.463
Uh. sorry. I'll go.

342
00:18:12.256 --> 00:18:13.465
See you around. Courtney.

343
00:18:14.675 --> 00:18:16.260
No. Stay.

344
00:18:16.593 --> 00:18:17.678
Have lunch.

345
00:18:17.761 --> 00:18:19.555
There's room for everybody.

346
00:18:21.223 --> 00:18:22.641
We were gonna talk about the dance.

347
00:18:22.933 --> 00:18:24.435
You're going. right?

348
00:18:25.477 --> 00:18:26.979
- Well. I...
- Can you drive?

349
00:18:27.062 --> 00:18:28.480
Because I'm restricted.

350
00:18:28.564 --> 00:18:31.859
and Courtney's dads are just strict.
and Ashley's car's old.

351
00:18:31.942 --> 00:18:34.028
- It's not that old.
- It's older than me.

352
00:18:37.906 --> 00:18:39.325
<i>A limo?</i>

353
00:18:39.408 --> 00:18:40.951
Honey. we can't afford a limo.

354
00:18:41.035 --> 00:18:43.579
- What were you thinking?
- How about we split it?

355
00:18:43.662 --> 00:18:45.622
I've got a bunch of money
saved from the Crestmont.

356
00:18:45.706 --> 00:18:47.291
A car for the night. with a driver?

357
00:18:47.374 --> 00:18:49.418
We're talking probably $500.
probably more.

358
00:18:49.501 --> 00:18:52.379
- Why don't you take the Jeep?
- The Jeep is a hundred years old.

359
00:18:52.463 --> 00:18:55.007
The Jeep's not a hundred years old.
It's not even paid off yet.

360
00:18:55.090 --> 00:18:56.759
Why don't you take the station wagon?

361
00:18:56.842 --> 00:18:58.719
'Cause that's so much better.

362
00:18:58.802 --> 00:19:01.055
You guys. I'm trying to have friends.

363
00:19:01.138 --> 00:19:03.182
you know. like you guys
are always talking about.

364
00:19:03.265 --> 00:19:05.934
Sweetie. your friends are not
going to like or dislike you for a car.

365
00:19:06.018 --> 00:19:08.145
Mom. it's high school.
Of course they will.

366
00:19:08.228 --> 00:19:09.772
Listen. I was in high school.

367
00:19:09.855 --> 00:19:12.441
Yeah. but you have no idea.
because you were popular. I'm not.

368
00:19:13.734 --> 00:19:14.568
Hannah.

369
00:19:14.651 --> 00:19:15.778
Yeah. well. it's true.

370
00:19:18.113 --> 00:19:19.323
Well. you were.

371
00:19:20.866 --> 00:19:22.284
No. The answer is no.

372
00:19:35.130 --> 00:19:36.924
They're coming to pick up the box.

373
00:19:40.177 --> 00:19:41.178
"Evidence."

374
00:19:43.764 --> 00:19:44.681
So clinical.

375
00:19:44.765 --> 00:19:45.641
Well...

376
00:19:46.809 --> 00:19:48.310
it's their label.

377
00:19:48.394 --> 00:19:51.480
Maybe we need to be looking
through her room again.

378
00:19:51.563 --> 00:19:52.940
We've been through...

379
00:19:53.023 --> 00:19:55.359
No. we threw things in a box.

380
00:19:55.442 --> 00:19:58.070
I mean. we need to dig deeper.

381
00:19:58.153 --> 00:19:59.571
There's something we're missing.

382
00:19:59.655 --> 00:20:01.240
They asked for schoolbooks.

383
00:20:01.323 --> 00:20:04.284
papers. photos. mementos.

384
00:20:04.368 --> 00:20:06.954
Let's let them start with this
and see what they say.

385
00:20:07.204 --> 00:20:08.539
It's a full carton.

386
00:20:33.814 --> 00:20:35.190
Ah. honey.

387
00:20:36.024 --> 00:20:37.109
Oh. you're beautiful.

388
00:20:37.276 --> 00:20:38.277
Dad.

389
00:20:38.902 --> 00:20:40.821
It's true.
I never looked so lovely for a dance.

390
00:20:40.904 --> 00:20:42.364
That's ridiculous.

391
00:20:42.448 --> 00:20:43.449
Hannah...

392
00:20:43.949 --> 00:20:47.661
you are the most beautiful woman
in this family.

393
00:20:48.745 --> 00:20:50.998
I'd agree. but I'd be in trouble
with both of you.

394
00:20:52.791 --> 00:20:53.750
Here you are.

395
00:20:53.834 --> 00:20:56.295
- Perfect.
- Aw. thanks. Dad. It's beautiful.

396
00:20:56.462 --> 00:20:58.088
Just a little smile.

397
00:20:58.172 --> 00:21:00.674
Aah! Oh. come on. now. There you go.

398
00:21:02.885 --> 00:21:04.595
Honey. and I'm sorry. I'm...

399
00:21:04.678 --> 00:21:06.638
I'm sorry we couldn't afford
to give you that limo.

400
00:21:06.722 --> 00:21:09.016
Mom. it's okay. really.

401
00:21:11.268 --> 00:21:12.102
Can I have the keys?

402
00:21:12.436 --> 00:21:13.645
You can.

403
00:21:14.021 --> 00:21:17.107
You just have to take off the tag...

404
00:21:18.066 --> 00:21:19.318
because...

405
00:21:24.031 --> 00:21:25.073
Andy.

406
00:21:25.157 --> 00:21:27.326
- You got a new car?
- You got a new car?

407
00:21:27.409 --> 00:21:29.161
I upgraded the lease.
It's a simple trade.

408
00:21:29.244 --> 00:21:30.871
- For the same payment?
- A bit more.

409
00:21:32.414 --> 00:21:35.125
It's worth it.
It's the winter formal. Liv.

410
00:21:35.501 --> 00:21:37.336
Oh. it's... it's great!

411
00:21:37.419 --> 00:21:39.338
- Thank you. Daddy.
- He's the hero. as always.

412
00:21:39.421 --> 00:21:40.631
You're the best.

413
00:21:40.714 --> 00:21:41.715
Go.

414
00:21:43.967 --> 00:21:45.886
Oh. wait. Wait. wait. wait. Be careful!

415
00:21:49.890 --> 00:21:50.974
Oh. my God!

416
00:21:53.477 --> 00:21:55.145
Well...

417
00:22:02.402 --> 00:22:04.238
I love this car.

418
00:22:04.905 --> 00:22:05.989
It has that new car smell.

419
00:22:06.532 --> 00:22:08.033
Oh. my God.

420
00:22:08.116 --> 00:22:10.536
Did your parents buy you
a new car for this dance?

421
00:22:10.619 --> 00:22:12.621
Um... Kind of.

422
00:22:12.704 --> 00:22:15.290
Holy crap! I didn't know you were rich!

423
00:22:15.916 --> 00:22:19.336
Oh. my God. Stephanie. you can
think that shit. but you can't say it.

424
00:22:22.130 --> 00:22:23.507
Oh... designated driver.

425
00:22:25.676 --> 00:22:26.552
Let's go in?

426
00:22:26.635 --> 00:22:28.136
Here we go!

427
00:22:48.615 --> 00:22:49.449
Thanks.

428
00:22:50.492 --> 00:22:51.493
Wow.

429
00:22:51.577 --> 00:22:52.536
I know. right?

430
00:22:52.619 --> 00:22:55.539
It took the sophomores. like. two days.
and I made them redo it twice.

431
00:22:55.622 --> 00:22:57.457
Looking good. ladies. Come on.

432
00:22:58.000 --> 00:22:59.001
That's perfect.

433
00:23:03.130 --> 00:23:04.131
Let's go dance.

434
00:23:08.010 --> 00:23:09.469
Seriously. Tyler?

435
00:23:09.553 --> 00:23:11.138
It's for the yearbook.

436
00:23:11.221 --> 00:23:13.056
I don't care. Don't put it in my face.

437
00:23:14.975 --> 00:23:15.976
Hannah.

438
00:23:16.059 --> 00:23:17.060
You look good.

439
00:23:19.521 --> 00:23:20.522
Hey.

440
00:23:20.647 --> 00:23:21.648
Hey.

441
00:23:22.524 --> 00:23:23.525
Who'd you come here with?

442
00:23:23.817 --> 00:23:25.277
Oh. just Courtney.

443
00:23:25.944 --> 00:23:26.778
And her court.

444
00:23:27.112 --> 00:23:28.238
The Courtnettes.

445
00:23:28.405 --> 00:23:29.406
Yeah.

446
00:23:29.906 --> 00:23:30.782
You?

447
00:23:31.116 --> 00:23:32.117
Big date?

448
00:23:32.200 --> 00:23:33.368
It was supposed to be.

449
00:23:34.661 --> 00:23:35.495
Hey.

450
00:23:35.579 --> 00:23:37.414
Uh. hey.

451
00:23:38.123 --> 00:23:39.708
I should... yeah.

452
00:23:43.003 --> 00:23:44.004
Uh...

453
00:23:44.379 --> 00:23:45.505
You look amazing.

454
00:23:45.839 --> 00:23:47.382
Good enough to make your next list?

455
00:23:48.550 --> 00:23:51.261
Look. I'll say. like. a million times
that I'm sorry.

456
00:23:51.345 --> 00:23:52.763
- Don't say it.
- I love you.

457
00:23:53.055 --> 00:23:54.723
You said it. Wow.

458
00:23:55.057 --> 00:23:56.933
- I'll say it again if that helps.
- No.

459
00:23:57.017 --> 00:23:58.977
Wait. wait. wait. wait. wait.

460
00:23:59.061 --> 00:24:00.646
Is this happening again?
You're back together?

461
00:24:00.729 --> 00:24:03.440
Not unless this is
the Hell Freezes Over dance.

462
00:24:03.523 --> 00:24:05.734
Sad thing is.
that'd be a really good theme.

463
00:24:07.486 --> 00:24:08.445
Later.

464
00:24:11.406 --> 00:24:13.784
Okay. seriously.
how does he get all the hot girls?

465
00:24:14.117 --> 00:24:15.160
I mean...

466
00:24:15.660 --> 00:24:17.496
his dick must be huge.

467
00:24:17.913 --> 00:24:20.874
Only one huge dick in the vicinity
at the moment. Bryce.

468
00:24:21.291 --> 00:24:23.043
Whoo! She's talking about you. big guy.

469
00:24:23.377 --> 00:24:24.419
Yeah. she is.

470
00:24:27.422 --> 00:24:28.715
Sorry about him.

471
00:24:29.257 --> 00:24:31.343
Lots of money. just no class.

472
00:24:31.635 --> 00:24:32.552
Right.

473
00:24:33.220 --> 00:24:34.304
You do look amazing. though.

474
00:24:44.606 --> 00:24:46.775
Hey. where'd you guys go?

475
00:24:47.150 --> 00:24:48.485
Oh. my God. I'm so sorry.

476
00:24:49.027 --> 00:24:50.862
We thought you were right behind us.

477
00:24:50.946 --> 00:24:52.155
Come dance with us.

478
00:24:56.785 --> 00:24:58.370
Well. hello there. ladies.

479
00:24:59.329 --> 00:25:02.624
So. are we gonna be seeing
an encore presentation tonight. or what?

480
00:25:02.791 --> 00:25:04.000
What are you talking about?

481
00:25:04.084 --> 00:25:06.753
You're gonna try and tell me that these
babes right here aren't you guys?

482
00:25:06.920 --> 00:25:09.589
Come on.
I know a fine piece when I see one.

483
00:25:10.006 --> 00:25:11.091
Or two.

484
00:25:11.174 --> 00:25:13.218
So. is this a thing now?
Did you guys come here together?

485
00:25:13.301 --> 00:25:16.263
We came as friends.
Maybe one day you'll have some.

486
00:25:28.108 --> 00:25:29.151
Oh. hey.

487
00:25:31.153 --> 00:25:33.405
Aren't you supposed to get on the mic
and say things like.

488
00:25:33.488 --> 00:25:35.824
"Hey. Liberty High. let's keep it tight!"

489
00:25:35.907 --> 00:25:38.535
I'm a legit deejay. not a birthday clown.

490
00:25:38.869 --> 00:25:40.120
Those aren't the only options.

491
00:25:40.454 --> 00:25:42.998
You see the world as binary.
It's a mosaic.

492
00:25:43.081 --> 00:25:43.915
Oh. God.

493
00:25:43.999 --> 00:25:45.751
Look at this mass of humanity.

494
00:25:46.251 --> 00:25:47.919
Hundreds of stories.

495
00:25:48.587 --> 00:25:49.755
It's kind of beautiful.

496
00:25:50.505 --> 00:25:51.590
And romantic.

497
00:25:52.424 --> 00:25:53.258
Yeah.

498
00:25:54.092 --> 00:25:55.135
Kind of is.

499
00:26:29.211 --> 00:26:30.045
Go.

500
00:26:31.671 --> 00:26:32.506
Go get her.

501
00:26:33.340 --> 00:26:34.549
Go get her and do what?

502
00:26:34.883 --> 00:26:36.343
It's a dance. right?

503
00:26:36.843 --> 00:26:38.762
Maybe dance with her?

504
00:26:39.346 --> 00:26:41.431
I can't... You know I can't dance.

505
00:26:41.640 --> 00:26:43.975
We talked about this when you
forced me to come tonight.

506
00:26:44.059 --> 00:26:45.852
Nobody can dance. Look.

507
00:26:46.728 --> 00:26:49.314
When people can dance at a dance.
nobody likes 'em.

508
00:26:49.397 --> 00:26:51.066
I didn't force you to come.

509
00:26:51.149 --> 00:26:53.902
We made a bet. and I got higher
than a "C." so you lost.

510
00:26:54.236 --> 00:26:55.320
Now. go.

511
00:26:56.279 --> 00:26:57.280
Come on.

512
00:27:11.837 --> 00:27:12.671
Clay.

513
00:27:14.422 --> 00:27:15.715
Clay!

514
00:27:17.300 --> 00:27:19.052
You're missing out on the fun run.

515
00:27:19.970 --> 00:27:22.764
It's three miles of torture.
What part of that is fun?

516
00:27:23.682 --> 00:27:24.975
Calling it fun is Orwellian.

517
00:27:25.767 --> 00:27:27.894
And why do you care if I miss it?

518
00:27:27.978 --> 00:27:29.604
Who else is gonna call it Orwellian?

519
00:27:38.238 --> 00:27:39.698
Are you sure you didn't run already?

520
00:27:40.156 --> 00:27:41.449
I had a late night.

521
00:27:42.409 --> 00:27:43.410
I'm aware.

522
00:27:46.454 --> 00:27:48.206
Listen. Clay.
what you did to Tyler. that's...

523
00:27:48.290 --> 00:27:49.874
I don't want to hear it. Tony.

524
00:27:52.460 --> 00:27:54.296
I feel you. brother. but still.

525
00:27:55.630 --> 00:27:57.007
